just listening to her.

27:41.029 --> 27:42.929
I wish she'd keep me after school.

27:42.931 --> 27:44.431
I swear

27:44.433 --> 27:46.233
that I did not have sex with Jordan

27:46.235 --> 27:48.135
until after he was 17.

27:48.137 --> 27:49.636
But you-you are pregnant.

27:49.638 --> 27:52.439
Well, was it an immaculate conception?

27:56.945 --> 27:59.946
It's not Jordan's baby.

28:05.020 --> 28:06.753
Order. Order.

28:06.755 --> 28:09.156
I will clear this courtroom.

28:10.041 --> 28:11.575
Jeffrey is the father.

28:12.377 --> 28:14.211
My ex.

28:14.213 --> 28:15.312
I don't like this surprise party.

28:15.314 --> 28:16.413
Jeffrey can't be the father.

28:16.415 --> 28:18.782
He was out of town in
the right timeframe.

28:18.784 --> 28:21.318
- Flew to D.C. on business.
- Or...

28:21.320 --> 28:22.652
Wait a minute.

28:22.654 --> 28:24.554
He went to Philly for a night.

28:24.556 --> 28:26.223
It's only a couple
hours outside New York.

28:26.225 --> 28:28.692
Check Susan's travel. See
if she was out of town.

28:30.796 --> 28:33.530
Credit card gas receipt
outside Philadelphia.

28:33.532 --> 28:35.132
Jeffrey's lost it.

28:35.134 --> 28:38.034
But Jordan...

28:38.036 --> 28:41.338
No.

28:41.340 --> 28:42.739
Susan told me she was pregnant.

28:42.741 --> 28:45.041
She and her husband had tried

28:45.043 --> 28:47.144
to make their relationship
work one last time.

28:47.146 --> 28:48.411
How did that make you feel?

28:48.413 --> 28:49.713
Scared.

28:49.715 --> 28:52.382
We had only been
together for a few weeks.

28:52.384 --> 28:56.036
But then I thought about
how much I loved her.

28:56.038 --> 28:57.604
I could raise the kid

28:57.606 --> 28:59.606
as the father. And since

28:59.608 --> 29:01.458
her husband couldn't make her happy,

29:01.460 --> 29:03.927
maybe I could. What would you say

29:03.929 --> 29:07.164
to those who think that
you're making a mistake?

29:07.166 --> 29:09.549
Mom, Dad,

29:09.551 --> 29:11.685
Susan makes me happy.

29:11.687 --> 29:14.487
And I think I deserve that,

29:14.489 --> 29:15.989
no matter what anybody says.

29:15.991 --> 29:17.657
No further questions.

29:18.546 --> 29:20.646
You've given up football,

29:20.671 --> 29:23.463
Hudson U. And is it not true

29:23.465 --> 29:27.067
that you recently turned down an
acceptance to City Arts College?

29:27.069 --> 29:29.603
I have to take care
of Susan and the baby.

29:29.605 --> 29:31.104
- I'll get a job.
- A job

29:31.106 --> 29:33.940
that only requires a high
school diploma, right?

29:33.942 --> 29:35.642
So you can raise a baby

29:35.644 --> 29:38.411
- that's not even yours?
- That baby will be mine.

29:38.413 --> 29:41.548
I'll raise it like it's my own.

29:42.935 --> 29:44.668
I did not see this coming.

29:44.670 --> 29:47.370
Let's dig into Edward. His
profile says he's with us,

29:47.372 --> 29:49.756
but I think we may be wrong about him.

29:51.660 --> 29:53.243
You were right about Edward.

29:53.245 --> 29:54.961
Cable tracked his last few days.

29:54.963 --> 29:58.415
I will give you one guess where
he went after Mass last night.

29:58.417 --> 30:01.676
Well, if I only have one
guess, I'm going with BDSM.

30:01.701 --> 30:03.418
I don't want to know how you knew that.

30:03.443 --> 30:06.206
Yes, he was at a
sadomasochism club until 3:00.

30:06.208 --> 30:08.575
So much for our beacon of morality.

30:08.577 --> 30:10.277
Edward's a classic reaction formation.

30:10.279 --> 30:12.879
He gets excited when a
repressed wish is expressed.

30:12.881 --> 30:17.150
So he might say Susan and
Jordan should burn in hell.

30:17.152 --> 30:18.718
But secretly wants to be Jordan.

30:18.720 --> 30:20.053
He's our wild card.

30:20.055 --> 30:23.089
We need a new strategy now
that we can't count on him.

30:23.091 --> 30:25.258
Also, see if Cable's had any luck

30:25.260 --> 30:27.227
with Susan's family.

30:27.229 --> 30:29.362
Might be a way in there.

30:29.364 --> 30:31.431
Hey. You good at breaking up fights?

30:31.433 --> 30:33.566
I'm better at it with
helmet and pads on.

30:33.568 --> 30:36.353
Well, suit up, 'cause I
think we're about to have one.

30:36.355 --> 30:38.004
- That's my child.
- You serious, man?

30:38.006 --> 30:39.606
You think you can raise my child?

30:39.608 --> 30:40.953
- We're still married!
- You want some more?

30:40.977 --> 30:41.918
I'll take you down!

30:41.943 --> 30:43.360
Calm down! Calm down!

30:43.362 --> 30:44.611
You want to be a man, right?

30:44.613 --> 30:45.612
- Right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

30:45.614 --> 30:46.646
How about you try

30:46.648 --> 30:48.715
being the bigger man?

30:51.453 --> 30:53.720
You're supposed to be the...

30:53.722 --> 30:55.388
calm in the storm.

30:55.390 --> 30:58.191
She has my child. She thinks the
two of them are gonna raise it?

30:58.193 --> 30:59.957
I'm gonna get full custody, you hear me?

30:59.982 --> 31:02.649
You're never gonna see
that baby, I promise you.

31:04.032 --> 31:06.166
Well, now he's the storm in the calm.

31:06.168 --> 31:09.469
And Wendy is explaining that he
has a good shot at getting custody.

31:09.471 --> 31:12.505
And she's not gonna
take that case pro bono.

31:12.507 --> 31:14.207
They are on their own.

31:14.209 --> 31:16.409
Jordan's never been under
this kind of pressure.

31:16.411 --> 31:18.645
What did Romeo and Juliet
do when overwhelming forces

31:18.647 --> 31:21.247
threatened to tear them apart?

31:21.249 --> 31:23.450
- They killed themselves.
- Before that.

31:25.020 --> 31:26.469
They ran.

31:26.471 --> 31:27.654
Yeah.

31:27.656 --> 31:30.090
Danny, let's keep an
eye on Jordan and Susan.

31:30.092 --> 31:33.226
I have a feeling they're
about to take a little trip.

31:35.547 --> 31:38.348
You know, it's hard to
find a guy I can talk to,

31:38.350 --> 31:41.184
loves UFC, gives me space.

31:41.186 --> 31:42.919
Gabe does that.

31:42.921 --> 31:46.323
But listening to the
testimony in this case,

31:46.325 --> 31:48.124
I never thought I was dating down.

31:48.126 --> 31:50.093
That's interesting.

31:50.095 --> 31:52.262
Gabe's an adult, isn't he?

31:52.264 --> 31:54.064
Yeah. But...

31:54.066 --> 31:56.232
I hired him.

31:56.234 --> 31:59.569
Freelance. You don't own
him... I don't think, do you?

31:59.571 --> 32:01.271
- No.
- Good.

32:01.273 --> 32:03.973
But I'm clearly in a
position of power over him,

32:03.975 --> 32:05.141
and he's young.

32:05.143 --> 32:07.043
I know who I am, what I like,

32:07.045 --> 32:10.080
but when I was Gabe's age,
I was still figuring it out.

32:10.082 --> 32:12.415
Danny, he's a talented photographer...

32:12.417 --> 32:15.118
and he knows what he wants...
He's figured that out.

32:15.120 --> 32:18.288
Yeah. And the way he looks at me...

32:18.290 --> 32:20.557
that's one of the
things I love about him.

32:20.559 --> 32:24.527
Sounds like he admires you.

32:24.529 --> 32:28.131
Do you admire him?

32:32.938 --> 32:34.704
How did you know Susan

32:34.706 --> 32:36.806
would pull up to a diner in New Jersey?

32:36.808 --> 32:38.341
Magic.

32:38.343 --> 32:40.243
And her sister lives in Trenton.

32:40.245 --> 32:42.612
She stops here every time she visits.

32:45.250 --> 32:46.449
Are you sure we'll be okay?

32:46.451 --> 32:47.884
We're gonna figure this out.

32:47.886 --> 32:48.918
- I mean...
- Okay?

32:52.724 --> 32:55.625
Welcome to the Garden State.

32:55.627 --> 32:56.893
I am calling my lawyer.

32:56.895 --> 32:59.195
Good. Then Danny can call the police.

32:59.197 --> 33:02.082
There's a federal law called
the Mann Act... makes it a felony

33:02.084 --> 33:04.284
to transport a minor across state lines

33:04.286 --> 33:06.820
with the intent to engage in sex.

33:06.822 --> 33:09.406
Susan, it's time

33:09.408 --> 33:11.207
you and I had a little chat.

33:27.085 --> 33:30.486
Federal prison's a lot worse
than a conversation with me.

33:30.488 --> 33:32.188
I promise.

33:34.225 --> 33:36.492
He's a good kid.

33:36.494 --> 33:39.095
He is more than just a kid.

33:39.097 --> 33:40.329
I know.

33:40.331 --> 33:41.764
I think Jordan...

33:41.766 --> 33:45.167
is a Balcony Person.

33:45.169 --> 33:46.635
What?

33:46.637 --> 33:49.338
Well, a Balcony Person
is someone who sits

33:49.340 --> 33:51.574
in the theater of your life,

33:51.576 --> 33:53.809
adoring you, admiring you,

33:53.811 --> 33:57.880
cheering you on, and
Jordan is that for you.

33:57.882 --> 34:01.317
Only... now he's lost
his balcony people...

34:01.319 --> 34:02.885
His parents,

34:02.887 --> 34:04.453
the ones cheering him on,

34:04.455 --> 34:07.676
the ones filling out his
college applications, and...

34:08.559 --> 34:10.860
Jordan needs that.

34:10.862 --> 34:12.862
Doesn't everyone need that?

34:12.864 --> 34:15.097
Sure.

34:15.099 --> 34:17.400
But some people never had
it growing up, so they have

34:17.402 --> 34:21.337
this insatiable need to fill
their balcony as grown-ups.

34:21.339 --> 34:23.706
I looked at your phone records...
You haven't talked to your dad

34:23.708 --> 34:24.974
in ten years.

34:24.976 --> 34:27.676
- He lives a long way away.
- He's not a bad man,

34:27.678 --> 34:29.978
from what I understand. Is he?

34:30.815 --> 34:32.915
But when he married your stepmother

34:32.917 --> 34:36.985
and his focus shifted to
her and her children...

34:36.987 --> 34:39.688
you felt like he left
your balcony, didn't you?

34:39.690 --> 34:41.824
I saw the way

34:41.826 --> 34:44.659
you looked at the wall when
Dr. Strand started talking

34:44.661 --> 34:46.195
about dating down.

34:46.197 --> 34:48.030
You wanted to escape.

34:48.032 --> 34:49.899
'Cause you know the man you need,

34:49.900 --> 34:51.367
the men that you've needed,

34:51.369 --> 34:53.936
they have to adore you,
put you on a pedestal.

34:53.938 --> 34:56.672
But they'll never be enough.

34:56.674 --> 34:59.942
Even your husband Jeffrey
wasn't enough, was he?

34:59.944 --> 35:02.578
So you found a young man, this boy,

35:02.580 --> 35:05.214
and he didn't just adore you, he...

35:05.216 --> 35:07.249
outright worshipped you.

35:07.251 --> 35:10.719
So much that he was willing
to give up going to college,

35:10.721 --> 35:13.789
and raise a child with you
that... that wasn't even his.

35:13.791 --> 35:17.359
Is that fair of you to
ask a 17-year-old boy?

35:17.361 --> 35:19.528
You're gonna be a mother.

35:19.530 --> 35:21.397
Okay?

35:21.399 --> 35:23.299
And that child is gonna

35:23.301 --> 35:24.934
adore you...

35:24.936 --> 35:26.569
and love you.

35:26.571 --> 35:28.037
And you will get to be

35:28.039 --> 35:29.939
his or her Balcony Person.

35:31.609 --> 35:33.542
I...

35:33.544 --> 35:35.811
I'm not very good...

35:35.813 --> 35:38.013
at being alone.

35:38.015 --> 35:39.215
You do have a husband.

35:39.217 --> 35:41.784
Listen...

35:43.221 --> 35:46.722
This is a woman who's a friend of mine.

35:46.724 --> 35:48.591
She's very nice.

35:48.593 --> 35:51.360
You should make an appointment.

35:52.597 --> 35:54.463
A shrink.

35:54.465 --> 35:56.131
You should make an appointment.

35:56.133 --> 35:58.734
God, what have I done?

36:02.306 --> 36:04.206
Dr. Bull...

36:04.208 --> 36:08.511
do you think that there is
such a thing as true love?

36:10.214 --> 36:11.981
I do.

36:11.983 --> 36:14.383
But this isn't it.

36:23.127 --> 36:24.593
Jordan.

36:25.863 --> 36:28.330
Susan has something she'd like to say.

36:28.332 --> 36:30.199
Jordan...

36:30.201 --> 36:32.701
I...

36:32.703 --> 36:34.370
got so caught up

36:34.372 --> 36:37.106
trying to run away from my...

36:37.108 --> 36:39.074
old life

36:39.076 --> 36:41.343
that I didn't fully

36:41.345 --> 36:43.279
think it through. Susan...

36:43.281 --> 36:45.281
No, just-just listen, okay?

36:45.283 --> 36:47.016
I...

36:49.554 --> 36:51.520
I hurt you.

36:51.522 --> 36:54.390
- No. No, you didn't.
- I did.

36:54.392 --> 36:55.925
I did.

36:55.927 --> 36:57.726
And...

36:57.728 --> 37:00.663
and this is not right.

37:00.665 --> 37:03.599
And you know that, and I know that.

37:03.601 --> 37:05.701
And I...

37:05.703 --> 37:08.637
am truly, truly sorry.

37:08.639 --> 37:11.173
Susan... n-no.

37:11.175 --> 37:13.008
I-I love you.

37:13.010 --> 37:14.376
Okay.

37:15.546 --> 37:17.313
Jordan...

37:17.315 --> 37:19.415
it's over.

37:19.417 --> 37:21.584
Please forgive me.

37:21.586 --> 37:24.086
Good-bye.

37:25.489 --> 37:26.956
No. No. Susan!

37:26.958 --> 37:28.591
- Susan!
- Come on. Let her go.

37:28.593 --> 37:30.259
You did this.

37:30.261 --> 37:31.961
What did you say to her?

37:31.963 --> 37:33.762
It's what she realized.

37:33.764 --> 37:35.864
She was using you to
make herself feel special.

37:35.866 --> 37:37.800
But it never would have been enough.

37:37.802 --> 37:40.536
Teaching wasn't enough.
Her husband wasn't enough.

37:40.538 --> 37:44.340
Nothing... would have ever been enough.

37:44.342 --> 37:47.076
Not for her. And it wasn't love.

37:47.078 --> 37:49.812
As much as it may have felt like it.

37:49.814 --> 37:51.647
She needs help.

37:53.217 --> 37:55.818
You'll feel this way again,

37:55.820 --> 37:57.486
with someone else...

37:57.488 --> 37:59.088
for the right reasons.

37:59.090 --> 38:02.157
Dr. Bull, I...

38:02.159 --> 38:03.659
Hey.

38:03.661 --> 38:05.094
I've been there.

38:15.172 --> 38:17.439
What if they don't listen?

38:17.441 --> 38:19.908
I can't promise they
will... But I know for a fact

38:19.910 --> 38:23.045
they won't listen if
you don't talk to them.

38:24.348 --> 38:26.682
But what I said on the stand...

38:26.684 --> 38:28.884
Just go over to them.

38:28.886 --> 38:31.253
Let it happen.

38:56.313 --> 38:58.647
I finally figured out what you meant...

38:58.649 --> 39:00.582
"winning the right way."

39:00.584 --> 39:02.985
Putting Jordan's family back together.

39:02.987 --> 39:05.487
Chunk...

39:05.489 --> 39:07.456
why did you really quit football?

39:07.458 --> 39:08.957
I told you.

39:10.594 --> 39:12.594
I didn't want to play anymore.

39:12.596 --> 39:13.896
That's all.

39:13.898 --> 39:15.064
I was done

39:15.066 --> 39:18.033
with the injuries, done
with the pressure...

39:18.035 --> 39:21.036
done with the thrill of
running the ball over the line.

39:21.038 --> 39:23.138
You get to a...

39:23.140 --> 39:26.208
certain point, you're
ready for a new challenge.

39:26.210 --> 39:28.844
I hear that.

39:28.846 --> 39:32.715
You try telling that to parents
the day before the draft.

39:32.717 --> 39:35.017
I always meant to tell her the truth.

39:35.019 --> 39:37.853
- I just never got the chance.
- Your mom,

39:37.855 --> 39:40.222
she was your biggest fan.

39:40.224 --> 39:41.224
Yeah.

39:43.160 --> 39:45.594
We all need one.

39:45.596 --> 39:49.031
Hey, thanks for putting me on this case.

39:50.634 --> 39:52.167
Who's yours?

39:52.169 --> 39:53.902
Who's your biggest fan?

39:53.904 --> 39:55.904
Isn't it you?

